reviews.text: Car park too small. New housing development and offices near by

Just parked up after being on wrong side of crossing. Ran around and was furiously pressing button on door of carriage whilst time was 10.51 and fifty odd seconds only for the train to pull away from in front of me as it turned 10.52. on this journey in these circumstances, was this reasonable? On this occasion what would it have matteted. To delay the train approx seconds.

Ok station with lots of trains (which has its ups and downs). Could do with a foot bridge as well as the level crossing because the level crossing is down approximately 48 minutes in an hour so it is a pain to get to platform 1 from the village side of the level crossing. In terms of facilities their is a ticket machine on platform 1 and a waiting shelter on both platforms and 2 benches on each platform and a sheltered bike rack on platform 1 with 3 spaces and a car park next to platform 1.Friendly staff on board the train. all in all ok experience. Will age 9
A basic railway station on the Airedale Line. Steam and diesel hauled charter trains pass through from time to time.
